You are building a production-ready Orders Management Admin Panel as a single self-contained React component (or Next.js page). The panel has three view modes that the admin can toggle between freely at any time without losing state. All three views share the same data, filters, and selection state.

────────────────────────────────────────
TECH STACK
────────────────────────────────────────
- React 18 + TypeScript
- Supabase JS v2 client (@supabase/supabase-js)
- TailwindCSS for all styling (no external component libraries)
- React Query (@tanstack/react-query) for data fetching and cache
- Zustand for shared UI state (selected orders, active view, filters)
- react-beautiful-dnd for Kanban drag-and-drop (Plan B only)
- date-fns for date formatting
- No other dependencies

────────────────────────────────────────
DATABASE SCHEMA (Supabase / PostgreSQL)
────────────────────────────────────────

Table: "Orders"
  id: uuid (PK)
  client_id: uuid → "Clients"(id) nullable
  guest_id: uuid nullable
  full_name: text
  phone_number: text
  address: text
  governorate_id: bigint → "GovernoratesShipping"(id)
  shipping_price: numeric(10,2)
  status: varchar(20) — one of: pending | paid | shipped | delivered | cancelled
  total_amount: numeric(10,2)
  discount: numeric(10,2)
  payment_method: varchar(20) — one of: credit_card | paypal | cash_on_delivery
  promocode_id: integer → promo_codes(id) nullable
  created_at: timestamptz
  updated_at: timestamptz

Table: "Order_items"
  id: bigint (PK)
  order_id: uuid → "Orders"(id)
  product_id: uuid → "Products"(id) nullable
  quantity: integer
  price: numeric(10,2)
  color: text nullable
  size: text nullable

Table: "Clients"
  id: uuid (PK)
  fullName: text
  nickName: text
  email: text
  phone: numeric
  avatarUrl: text
  address: text
  governorateId: bigint

Table: "GovernoratesShipping"
  id: bigint (PK)
  governorateEn: text
  governorateAr: text
  shippingPrice: double precision

Table: "Carts"
  id: uuid (PK)
  client_id: uuid nullable → "Clients"(id)
  guest_id: text nullable
  items: jsonb (array of {product_id, quantity, price, color, size, name, image})
  created_at: timestamptz
  updated_at: timestamptz

────────────────────────────────────────
GLOBAL SHARED STATE (Zustand store)
────────────────────────────────────────

Create a single Zustand store called useOrdersStore with:

  activeView: 'table' | 'kanban' | 'detail'  — current view mode
  selectedIds: Set<string>                     — selected order UUIDs for bulk ops
  filters: {
    search: string                             — matches full_name, phone_number, order id
    status: string                             — '' means all
    payment: string                            — '' means all
    governorate: string                        — '' means all
    dateFrom: string                           — ISO date string
    dateTo: string                             — ISO date string
  }
  activeOrderId: string | null                 — the order currently open in detail panel

Actions:
  setView(view)
  toggleSelect(id)
  selectAll(ids)
  clearSelection()
  setFilter(key, value)
  resetFilters()
  setActiveOrder(id)

────────────────────────────────────────
DATA FETCHING (React Query)
────────────────────────────────────────

useOrdersQuery(filters):
  Fetches from "Orders" joined with:
    - "GovernoratesShipping" (for governorateEn + shippingPrice)
    - "Clients" (for fullName, email, phone)
  Applies filters from the Zustand store
  Returns: Order[] sorted by created_at desc
  Cache key: ['orders', filters]
  Stale time: 30 seconds

useOrderDetailQuery(orderId):
  Fetches single order with full join:
    - "Order_items" joined with "Products" (nameEn, images[0])
    - "Clients"
    - "GovernoratesShipping"
    - promo_codes (code, discount_value)
  Only runs when orderId is not null
  Cache key: ['order', orderId]

useCartsQuery():
  Fetches all "Carts" joined with "Clients" (fullName, email)
  Sorted by updated_at desc
  Cache key: ['carts']
  Stale time: 60 seconds

useOrderStatsMemo(orders):
  A useMemo that derives from the orders array:
    totalOrders: number
    totalRevenue: number (sum of total_amount where status !== 'cancelled')
    pendingCount: number
    paidCount: number
    shippedCount: number
    deliveredCount: number
    cancelledCount: number

useBulkStatusMutation():
  Takes: { ids: string[], newStatus: string }
  Runs: supabase.from("Orders").update({ status: newStatus }).in('id', ids)
  On success: invalidates ['orders'] cache, calls clearSelection()

useSingleStatusMutation():
  Takes: { id: string, newStatus: string }
  Runs: supabase.from("Orders").update({ status: newStatus }).eq('id', id)
  On success: invalidates ['orders'] and ['order', id] cache

────────────────────────────────────────
STATUS CONSTANTS
────────────────────────────────────────

Define a STATUSES array in order:
  [
    { key: 'pending',   label: 'Pending',   color: 'amber' },
    { key: 'paid',      label: 'Paid',      color: 'blue'  },
    { key: 'shipped',   label: 'Shipped',   color: 'purple'},
    { key: 'delivered', label: 'Delivered', color: 'green' },
    { key: 'cancelled', label: 'Cancelled', color: 'red'   },
  ]

Define a STATUS_NEXT map for the "advance to next" shortcut:
  pending   → paid
  paid      → shipped
  shipped   → delivered
  delivered → null (terminal)
  cancelled → null (terminal)

Define a Tailwind color map per status key for badges, backgrounds, and text:
  Use consistent classes like: bg-amber-50 text-amber-800 for pending, etc.

────────────────────────────────────────
TOP-LEVEL COMPONENT: <OrdersPage />
────────────────────────────────────────

Layout: full height flex-col

Render in this order:

1. <StatsBar />         — always visible, 5 stat cards
2. <Toolbar />          — always visible, search + filters + view toggle + bulk bar
3. <ViewRenderer />     — switches between the 3 views based on activeView

────────────────────────────────────────
COMPONENT: <StatsBar />
────────────────────────────────────────

A horizontal row of 5 metric cards derived from useOrderStatsMemo:
  - Total orders (neutral)
  - Revenue in EGP/$ (green)
  - Pending count (amber, clickable → sets filter status=pending)
  - Shipped count (purple, clickable → sets filter status=shipped)
  - Cancelled count (red, clickable → sets filter status=cancelled)

Each card: muted label on top, large bold number below.
Clicking a status card filters the order list to that status.

────────────────────────────────────────
COMPONENT: <Toolbar />
────────────────────────────────────────

Row 1 — Filters:
  - Search input (debounced 300ms) → updates filters.search
  - Status select dropdown → updates filters.status
  - Payment method select → updates filters.payment
  - Governorate select (populated from useGovernoratesQuery) → filters.governorate
  - Date range: two date inputs (from / to) → filters.dateFrom, filters.dateTo
  - "Reset filters" button (only visible when any filter is active)

Row 2 — View toggle + Bulk bar:
  Left side: 3 toggle buttons for view modes:
    [Table] [Kanban] [Detail]
    Active view button is visually highlighted.

  Right side (only visible when selectedIds.size > 0):
    "{N} orders selected"
    Status dropdown: "Move to..." → the 5 statuses minus cancelled
    [Apply bulk] button → calls useBulkStatusMutation
    [Clear selection] button

────────────────────────────────────────
VIEW A: <TableView />
────────────────────────────────────────

A full-width table with these columns (table-layout: fixed):
  [ ] checkbox | Order ID | Client | Total | Status | Payment | Governorate | Date | Actions

Header row:
  - Master checkbox: checks/unchecks all currently visible orders

Each data row:
  - Checkbox: calls toggleSelect(order.id)
  - Order ID: monospace font, truncated UUID (first 8 chars + "…"), copy-to-clipboard on click
  - Client: full_name bold, phone_number below in muted small text. If client_id is null, show "Guest" badge
  - Total: formatted currency
  - Status: colored badge using STATUS color map
  - Payment: pill badge (COD / Card / PayPal)
  - Governorate: governorateEn
  - Date: formatted with date-fns (e.g. "Apr 15, 2026")
  - Actions column:
      [View] button → sets activeOrderId + switches view to 'detail'
      Status inline select dropdown → calls useSingleStatusMutation on change
        The dropdown only shows valid next statuses (not backwards, not same status)
        Delivered and Cancelled orders show a disabled "—" instead

Empty state: centered illustration + "No orders found" + "Reset filters" button

Loading state: skeleton rows (5 rows of animated gray bars)

Pagination:
  Page size: 20 orders per page
  Bottom bar: "Showing X–Y of Z" + Prev / page numbers / Next
  Pagination is client-side from the React Query result

────────────────────────────────────────
VIEW B: <KanbanView />
────────────────────────────────────────

A horizontal flex row of 5 columns, one per status.
The board is scrollable horizontally if needed.

Each column (<KanbanColumn />):
  Header: status label + count badge (colored per status)
  Body: vertically scrollable list of <KanbanCard /> items
  Each column only shows orders matching that status (filtered from the full orders array)

Each <KanbanCard />:
  - Checkbox top-left: calls toggleSelect
  - Drag handle top-right (⠿ icon): enables react-beautiful-dnd
  - Order ID (truncated monospace)
  - Client name bold, governorate + payment method below
  - Total amount
  - Date
  - Status advance button (only if STATUS_NEXT[status] exists):
      Label: "Mark as [next status] →"
      On click: calls useSingleStatusMutation({ id, newStatus: STATUS_NEXT[status] })
  - [View details] text link → sets activeOrderId + switches to 'detail' view

Drag and drop behavior (react-beautiful-dnd):
  - Dragging a card to another column calls useSingleStatusMutation
  - Cannot drag to 'cancelled' (cancelled is drop-disabled)
  - Cannot drag backwards (paid → pending is not allowed). 
    Enforce with a canDrop(fromStatus, toStatus) check using the STATUSES order index.
  - Optimistic UI: update the local cache immediately, revert on error

Cancelled column:
  Cards are rendered at 60% opacity
  No drag handle, no advance button
  Only shows [View details] link

Empty column state: dashed border placeholder "No orders"

────────────────────────────────────────
VIEW C: <DetailView />
────────────────────────────────────────

A two-pane horizontal layout:

LEFT PANE (fixed 280px width, scrollable):
  Top: mini stats row (Total / Pending / Shipped / Revenue) — same data as StatsBar but compact

  Bulk bar (visible when selectedIds.size > 0):
    "{N} selected" + status dropdown + [Apply] button

  Order list items — one per order, each showing:
    - Checkbox
    - Client name (bold) + order ID (muted mono below)
    - Delivery info: governorate · payment · date (small muted)
    - Right side: total amount + status badge
    - Selected state: teal/green background highlight
    - Click anywhere on row (except checkbox): sets activeOrderId

RIGHT PANE (flex-1, scrollable):
  If no activeOrderId: centered empty state "Select an order to view details"

  If activeOrderId is set, render <OrderDetailPanel orderId={activeOrderId} />:

    Section 1 — Header:
      Client name (large, bold) + truncated order ID in mono below
      Right side action buttons:
        [Print invoice] → window.print() with a print-specific CSS class
        [Cancel order] → calls useSingleStatusMutation({ id, newStatus: 'cancelled' })
          Only visible if status is not already cancelled or delivered

    Section 2 — Status stepper:
      A horizontal pipeline of the 4 non-cancelled statuses: Pending → Paid → Shipped → Delivered
      Past statuses: green filled circle with checkmark
      Current status: teal filled, bold label
      Future statuses: gray outline circle
      Each future status step is clickable → calls useSingleStatusMutation
      If order is cancelled: show a separate red "Cancelled" badge instead of the stepper

    Section 3 — Client & delivery info (key-value rows):
      Client name (linked to client page if client_id exists)
      Phone number
      Full address
      Governorate + shipping price
      Payment method
      Promo code (if promocode_id exists): code string + discount amount

    Section 4 — Order items table:
      Thumbnail image (images[0] from Products), product name, color, size, quantity, unit price, subtotal
      Total row at bottom: subtotal + shipping - discount = total_amount

    Section 5 — Carts tab:
      A secondary tab strip inside the right pane: [Order Details] [Carts]
      Switching to Carts tab renders <CartsPanel /> which shows:
        A list of all active carts from useCartsQuery
        Each cart row: client name or "Guest (guest_id truncated)", item count, total value, last updated
        Clicking a cart row expands it inline to show cart items (product name, qty, price, color, size)
        [Clear cart] button per row: deletes the cart row from Supabase
        No pagination needed — carts are typically low volume

────────────────────────────────────────
SHARED BEHAVIORS ACROSS ALL 3 VIEWS
────────────────────────────────────────

1. Filter state is always live:
   All 3 views read from the same Zustand filters.
   Switching views never resets filters.

2. Selection state is always live:
   Checking a box in TableView, then switching to KanbanView,
   the card in KanbanView must also appear checked.
   selectedIds is a Set in Zustand shared across all views.

3. Bulk action bar:
   Always rendered inside <Toolbar /> regardless of view.
   Applies to whichever view is active.

4. Status mutation feedback:
   On any status change (single or bulk):
     Show a toast notification: "Status updated to [X]" (green)
     On error: "Failed to update. Try again." (red)
   Use a simple custom useToast hook (no external library).

5. Optimistic updates:
   For single status changes: update React Query cache immediately before Supabase responds.
   On error: rollback cache to previous value.

6. Real-time updates (optional but recommended):
   Subscribe to Supabase realtime on the "Orders" table.
   On INSERT or UPDATE: invalidate ['orders'] query automatically.
   This keeps all 3 views in sync if another admin is working simultaneously.

7. Empty and loading states:
   Every view must handle: loading (skeleton), empty (illustration + message), error (retry button).

